# FE Light Mode Readability Rule

## Hard Rule
- Neon foreground text on light surfaces is banned.
- Banned pairings include `text-primary`, `text-highlight`, `text-accent` on `bg-white`, `bg-neutral-*`, `bg-[var(--color-surface)]`, `bg-[var(--color-background)]`, and other light fills.

## Allowed Neon Usage
- Neon/accent colors are allowed for:
  - decorative icons, dots, and non-text accents,
  - dark-surface contexts with sufficient contrast,
  - large display-only emphasis where readability remains clear.

## Required Text Defaults On Light Surfaces
- Primary content: `text-neutral-900`
- Secondary content: `text-neutral-800` or `text-neutral-700`
- Meta/labels: `text-neutral-700` or `text-neutral-600`
- Links/buttons must keep readable hover states (no neon-on-light body text).

## Bad vs Good
- Bad: `bg-[var(--color-surface)] text-primary`
- Good: `bg-[var(--color-surface)] text-neutral-900`
- Bad: `bg-neutral-100 text-highlight`
- Good: `bg-neutral-100 text-neutral-800`

## Reviewer Checklist
- No neon text on light cards, tables, forms, chat bubbles, or muted panels.
- Action labels and metadata remain readable in light mode.
- Dark mode behavior is preserved after any light-mode readability change.
